= Twisted API Documentation =

This page describes how to generate the API docs for the Twisted web site.

You will need a checkout of the latest release of Twisted.

== Steps ==

 1. In a checkout of !WebSite (<svn://svn.twistedmatrix.com/svn/WebSite/trunk>), in the trunk/vhosts/twistedmatrix.com/documents/current directory, run:
{{{
% pydoctor -c twisted.cfg -o twisted-doc-model
...
% bzip2 twisted-doc-model 
% svn commit twisted-doc-model.bz2
}}}

 This will generate API documentation for the latest release of Twisted.  

 2. If there has been a new release, edit {{{twisted.cfg}}} to point to that release.

 3. Now, ssh to pyramid.

{{{
% sudo su - www-data
% pwd
/var/www
% svn up WebSite
% cd WebSite/vhosts/twistedmatrix.com
% ./generate-apidocs.sh newapi
}}}

 4. Look at the output in {{{documents/current/newapi}}} and make sure it looks alright, then replace the existing documentation:

{{{
#!sh
% mkdir documents/<old version number>
% mv documents/current/api documents/<old version number>/
% mv documents/current/newapi documents/current/api
}}}

 5. If there have been useful pydoctor changes, make sure to update your pydoctor checkout/installation on both hosts before running it.

